                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281023-152-off903 t18281023-152-crimeloc905"></join>, opposite to Mr. Thomas Byers, who is a <rs id="t18281023-152-viclabel906" type="occupation">cheesemonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281023-152-victim842 t18281023-152-viclabel906"></join>. On the 4th of October I saw the prisoner come and take<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182810230068"></xptr>a piece of bacon from his shop-window - he did not go into the shop, but went on the steps of a private-door, and took it round some casks; he put it under his coat - I ran and took him; he dropped it at my feet - I chased him to No. 2, Little Exeter-street; he ran into a house, where the door was open and shut the door in my face - I then returned and went to my work.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281023-152-person844">
